      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "HAPPY TOO YA (2) enjoyed the drop in class from the city when he took advantage of the inside barrier to lead and score by 6.7 metres at this venue last week. Goes up in grade but can push forward again from this favourable starting position. NOTHINGBUTWAVES (8) has been racing well and kept the ball rolling last time when a nose from the winner in second. That gave her a win and two placings from her last three outings here. Draws for a trail and can be dangerous if she gets the gaps. ULTIMATE WEAPON NZ (3) has been producing some decent efforts from tough draws of late, clocking in second from the back row the last time he raced here. Better served by this barrier. MAC THUNDER (10) cops a second row draw this time but did a good job in winning at this circuit and distance last week.",
